title: Add CPU Generation output
body:
What do you think about adding a display of the minimum Intel CPU architecture generation that supports all the instruction set extensions found in the file? This could make it easier to infer the target CPU that a binary was built for.

Here's an attempt at a PR to do so.

Example of the changed output:

```
$ ./target/debug/elfx86exts ./target/debug/elfx86exts
MODE64 (push)
CMOV (cmove)
MMX (paddb)
CPU Generation: Intel Core
```

This could be an optional output enabled by a `-g` option or similar if you don't want it displayed by default.

title: Bump memmap from 0.6.2 to 0.7.0
